    <div class="wpd-comment-text">
    <p>Not spelling. You’re thinking in English, I’m asking for someone fluent enough in Japanese. Back in the Orc Empire arc, there was confusion on Van’s gender because in Japanese, the “Miko” of his title could mean “Holy Son” or “Shrine Maiden.” I’m asking if this situation is similar, more like “Are the two titles different words in Katakana (or Hiragana/Kanji, etc.), but are just translated to us in English as the same words to reduce confusion?” That’s why I’m asking for someone who can read the raws or Yoshi for clarification. Because I do think it’d be interesting for someone<span id="wpdiscuz-readmore-16594_16581"><span class="wpdiscuz-hellip">… </span><span class="wpdiscuz-readmore" title="Read more »">Read more »</span></span></p>
