    <div class="wpd-comment-date">
    <i class="far fa-clock" aria-hidden="true"></i>
    August 14, 2021 1:19 am
</div>
</div>
    <div class="wpd-comment-text">
    <p>Holy Mother of Victory is “勝利の聖母”. Holy Mother Killer is “聖母殺し”. The term for Holy Mother is “聖母” in both cases. Anyone capable of reading kanji (which are mostly Chinese characters with a few unique to Japanese thrown in) would read this as “Holy Mother”. A modern Japanese person would normally associate this as a reference to the Virgin Mary in Catholicism, as this is the most prevalent usage today. The people of Lambda are not widely literate in Kanji and do not have any contact with Catholicism. Thus many of them would need contextual cues to even realize that<span id="wpdiscuz-readmore-20441_16594"><span class="wpdiscuz-hellip">… </span><span class="wpdiscuz-readmore" title="Read more »">Read more »</span></span></p>
</div>
    <div class="wpd-comment-footer">
    <div class="wpd-vote">
